dencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying setup and guidance**\\n\\nI need to specify that guidance says no Docker and to use loopback while ensuring that JSON is the only format. I should also mention that no extra Maven dependencies or Docker are allowed. The summary can note that version 5.0.1 resolves to Netty 4.2.2.Final, indicating good compatibility. Additionally, I have to emphasize that guidance should include environment variables and system properties in the agent guidance, but avoid restating deterministic entries. There's also the question of whether to include risks related to optional dependencies.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Vert.x Web Client 5.0.1 resolves to Vert.x Core 5.0.1 and Netty 4.2.2.Final; the existing 5.0.0 scaffold already needs Netty/JDK 25 native-run system properties, but its condition is pinned to 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runtime tests on JDK 25, ensure the generated test setup applies nativeTest/runtime system properties for 5.0.1 as well: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Meaningful WebClient coverage can use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer on loopback; no Docker service or external endpoint is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The public OAuth2WebClient API depends on optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2; avoid OAuth2-specific tests unless that optional dependency is intentionally added.\",\n    \"External HTTP services would make tests flaky; use local loopback servers for request, redirect, cookie, form, multipart, and streaming coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_027bf429a88f34ca016a40edf8c8248197906c642eb186bc33\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 809, "output": 775, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 3